# Optimal Solution (Trie)

## Observation

Instead of repeatedly comparing prefixes,

store all words in a Trie.

While inserting,

count how many words pass through each node.

Then

A prefix becomes unique when its node's count becomes **1**.

---

# Main Idea

Each Trie node stores

```
children

count
```

Whenever a word passes through a node

```
count += 1
```

Later

While searching

The first node whose count becomes

```
1
```

means

Only one word reaches this node.

Hence

That prefix is unique.

---

